I have some verilog code as below:

```
module cpu_top (
    /*verilator lint_off UNUSEDSIGNAL*/
    input clk, 
    /*verilator lint_on UNUSEDSIGNAL*/
    input rst
);

    logic [CPU_BITS-1:0] rda, rdb, rdx, result; 
    logic zero;

    op_t aluDecode;

    alu ALU0 (.rst(rst), .aluDecode(aluDecode), .a(rda), .b(rdx), .result(result), .zero(zero));

endmodule
```

I want to test this as I piece the top together but I can't drive these internal signals (rda, rdx, aluDecode) from my c++ testbench for cpu_top.

How can I drive these signals from the c++ testbench? I've tried /*verilator public*/ but I still get the signal not driven warning.

Thanks
